AN ACT relating to insurance; repealing provisions which prohibit
an insurer from issuing or renewing a policy of liability
insurance that contains certain provisions; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law establishes the Nevada Insurance Code which governs contracts of
2 insurance. (Title 57 of NRS) This bill repeals provisions of existing law that
3 prohibit an insurer from issuing or renewing a policy of liability insurance that
4 contains a provision that: (1) reduces the limit of liability stated in the policy by the
5 costs of defense, legal costs and fees and other expenses for claims; or (2)
6 otherwise limits the availability of coverage for the costs of defense, legal costs and
7 fees and other expenses for claims. (NRS 679A.210)
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 679A.210 is hereby repealed.
